---
title: DONE subtree execution can't find blocks in other sub-trees
layout: default
---

<div id="outline-container-1" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="sec-1"><span class="done DONE"> DONE</span> subtree execution can't find blocks in other sub-trees </h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-1">

<ul>
<li>
State "DONE"       from "TODO" <span class="timestamp-wrapper"> <span class="timestamp">2010-06-07 Mon 17:39</span></span>
</li>
<li>
State "TODO"       from "" <span class="timestamp-wrapper"> <span class="timestamp">2009-12-30 Wed 17:05</span></span>
</li>
</ul>


<p>
This is most likely due to the fact that `org-babel-execute-subtree'
calls `org-narrow-to-subtree', which narrows the buffer making
functions defined in other sub-trees invisible.  This is demonstrated
by calling `org-babel-execute-subtree' (bound to C-c M-b s) inside of
"tree 2" below.
</p>
<p>
Thanks to Tom Dye for pointing this out.
</p>

</div>

<div id="outline-container-1_1" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="sec-1_1">example </h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1_1">


</div>

<div id="outline-container-1_1_1" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1_1_1">tree 1 </h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1_1_1">





<div class="org-src-container"><label class="org-src-name">foo()</label><pre class="src src-R">
a <span class="org-constant">&lt;-</span> 1
</pre></div>



</div>

</div>

<div id="outline-container-1_1_2" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="sec-1_1_2">tree 2 </h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1_1_2">




<pre class="src src-R">a <span class="org-constant">&lt;-</span> 1
a + 1
</pre>




<pre class="src src-R">a + 2
</pre>


</div>
</div>
